A 400-Level University of Lagos (UNILAG) student from the Department of Pharmacy, Ahmed Olasunkanmi, has received the PANSITE of the Year award. He was rewarded for being a pharmacy student actively involved in public health advocacy, community development and demonstration of innovation in healthcare delivery, amongst other attributes. The PANSITE award, coined from the acronym PANS (Pharmaceutical Association of Nigerian Students), recognises outstanding pharmacy students in Nigeria.